  "title": "Temp Admin Support (13-weeks; hourly-rated)",
  "description": "<p><em><strong>Job Responsibilities:</strong></em></p><ul><li>Data Management: Perform accurate data entry, verification, and consolidation of information for incoming SEN (Special Educational Needs) students.</li><li>Data Cleaning & Analysis: Review, organise, and analyse SEN student data to support reporting and planning.</li><li>Stakeholder Communication: Liaise with students and parents to follow up on submission of required documents, ensuring completeness of records.</li><li>Event Support: Assist in the preparation and on-site coordination of SEN student and parent engagement events, including logistics and administrative support for the department.</li></ul><p><em><strong>Pre-requisites:</strong></em></p><ul><li>Strong attention to detail and proficiency in Microsoft Excel and basic data analysis tools.</li><li>Good written and verbal communication skills; comfortable ·       making phone calls to parents and students.</li><li>Organised, proactive, and able to manage multiple tasks independently within tight timelines.</li><li>Empathetic and professional when engaging with parents and students in sensitive contexts.</li></ul><p><br /></p><p><em><strong>Working Hours:</strong></em></p><ul><li>08:30am - 06:00pm, Mon - Fri</li><li>No duty on Weekends or Public Holiday</li></ul><p><em>Kindly note that this is an hourly paid position.</em></p>",
